				 Ire at NAZI bedspreads
																								Mumbai, Sept. 30 (Reuters): The Jewish community is up in arms against a home furnishing maker that has named its new line of bedspreads NAZI and used the swastika in its promotional brochure.																								The dealer says the word NAZI stands for New Arrival Zone of India, but Jewish leaders said the name sm-acked of Hitlers anti-Semitic regime. We will ask him to stop this nonsense, Jonathan Solomon of the Indian Jewish Federation said today. 
